<h2>How Can We Prevent GBV?</h2>

<ul>
    <li>Educate people about respect, consent, and equality.</li>
    <li>Speak out against abuse and harmful behavior.</li>
    <li>Create safe school environments.</li>
    <li>Teach men and boys how to respect and treat women.</li>
    <li>Encourage bystander action.</li>
    <li>Teach women and girls how they can protect themselves.</li>
    <li>Create organizations that give people more knowledge about <b>GBV.</b></li>
    <li>Teach young kids about safe and unsafe touches.</li>
    <li>Support victims and encourage them to seek help.</li>
    <li>Promote healthy relationships in communities and schools.</li>
</ul>

<a href="https://youtu.be/IYmBOTi1d9U?si=o8pssjD_VvkSzsZu">Learn More about Preventing GBV</a>

<h3>Raising Awareness About Gender-Based Violence</h3>

<p>
    <b>Raising awareness about Gender-Based Violence (GBV)</b> is one of the most important steps in preventing it.
    Many people experience abuse in silence because they do not fully understand what GBV is,
    or they are afraid to speak out.
</p>

<a href="https://youtu.be/dIFZYDVc5Gg?si=MhvP_15JKrSt8guO">
    Learn how to raise awareness about GBV
</a>

<p>
    Awareness helps people recognize that GBV is not only physical abuse,
    but also includes <b>emotional, verbal, sexual, and financial harm.</b>
</p>

